mic report collection starts. While the MultipartPostMethodTest executes addParameter with FilePart, it's still uncovered.\\n\\nI wonder if Jacoco or the dynamic report is excluding static initializers. It also seems like the agent may not record when Class.forName is called on the same class currently loading. Maybe the MethodHandle invocation isn't going through the bytecode instrumentation.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating coverage issues**\\n\\nI'm wondering about the Class.forName inside the class$ method and if it's still included in the bytecode. Maybe the line numbers aren't available, which would affect the coverage count. I should check the generated test to see if it wasn't included in git; it appears untracked but is there. \\n\\nIf the external run included the file, and attempts were used, it seems nothing is covered. It could be due to a lack of reachability metadata for MethodHandles.privateLookupIn, leading to a failed test. Maybe unsuccessful attempts just don't count for coverage.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_2S25Cd5n3z8OXKgq3GoSdYwV|fc_05b431e77857cb6d016a04a53ad0108196aa2dd670043cd593", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/commons-httpclient/commons-httpclient/3.0/build/test-results -type f -name '*.xml' -maxdepth 3 | xargs grep -n \"FilePartTest\\|legacyClass\" -C 2 2>/dev/null || true"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2140, "output": 1110, "cacheRead": 35840, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 39090, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778689310773, "responseId": "resp_05b431e77857cb6d016a04a51fe644819696d97579afe8cc4a"}}
